JK.

13:49.996 --> 13:51.729
<i>The Soccer Formal!</i>

13:51.731 --> 13:53.464
<i>So, without further ado...</i>

13:53.466 --> 13:55.500
I give you Michelle!

13:58.404 --> 13:59.937
[Button clicking]
[Feedback]

13:59.939 --> 14:03.074
-Soccer Formal tix
are offish on sale.

14:03.076 --> 14:05.409
<i>There's a sign-up sheet
inside the caf.</i>

14:05.411 --> 14:07.945
<i>I will be announcing the theme
later this week</i>

14:07.947 --> 14:10.282
<i>so make sure you write in
a suggestion.</i>

14:10.284 --> 14:12.550
Oh, and make them
good this year,

14:12.552 --> 14:14.353
for once.

14:14.355 --> 14:15.753
-I know it's kinda cliché, but

14:15.755 --> 14:17.156
I really wanted to go
to the dance.

14:17.158 --> 14:18.689
-Me too, girl.

14:18.691 --> 14:20.358
Hey, worse comes to worse,

14:20.360 --> 14:21.926
I'll be your date.

14:21.928 --> 14:24.162
-What? You with<i> moi</i>?

14:24.164 --> 14:25.630
I'd be honored!

14:25.632 --> 14:27.131
[Giggles]

14:29.836 --> 14:31.502
[Feedback]

14:31.504 --> 14:33.305
<i>-Uh, one more thing, guys.</i>

14:33.307 --> 14:35.974
<i>This is probably nothing,</i>
<i>but the police got</i> a call

14:35.976 --> 14:38.076
from Tate Hudson's father.

14:38.078 --> 14:40.245
<i>Tate appears to be
missing this morning.</i>

14:40.247 --> 14:43.048
<i>If anyone has seen him today,
come to my office!</i>

14:43.050 --> 14:46.617
<i>And you know me:
my office hours are every hour.</i>

14:47.086 --> 14:49.787
-EGGS: Statistically,
it's nearly impossible

14:49.789 --> 14:51.789
to find a missing person
after 72 hours.

14:51.791 --> 14:54.058
If a person's been missing
for more than seven years,

14:54.060 --> 14:55.893
in some states, they can be
legally declared deceased.

14:55.895 --> 14:57.429
-Jeez, Eggs.

14:57.431 --> 14:59.163
<i>-Tate is probably fine.</i>

14:59.165 --> 15:01.399
-I heard that
he left the party crying.

15:01.401 --> 15:04.202
-I heard he has a side piece
in the city.

15:04.204 --> 15:05.336
-Oh, my gosh!

15:05.338 --> 15:07.405
-You have a
safe and beautiful day,

15:07.407 --> 15:09.173
Fighting Ferrets!

15:09.175 --> 15:11.108
Squeak, squeak!
[Thunder crashing]

15:11.110 --> 15:12.644
-Ow! Oh!

15:14.112 --> 15:15.813
-Sorry! Nothing! Sorry.

15:16.148 --> 15:18.482
-What was that outburst?
Are you okay?

15:18.484 --> 15:20.017
-Yeah. This is
going to sound crazy,

15:20.019 --> 15:21.752
but every time
the lightning flashes,

15:21.754 --> 15:23.287
I get a spasm in my leg.

15:23.289 --> 15:24.923
-Tate?

15:24.925 --> 15:26.557
Where the hell are you?

15:26.993 --> 15:28.959
-You don't think
we did that, right?

15:28.961 --> 15:32.230
-Ha! I wish we had the power
to make assholes disappear!

15:34.133 --> 15:35.633
[Malevolent music]

15:35.635 --> 15:37.068
[Tate sobbing]

15:41.306 --> 15:42.740
[Tears dripping]

15:45.978 --> 15:47.845
-I don't need a fashion fund.

15:47.847 --> 15:50.181
I've already got
the hottest new accessory.

15:50.183 --> 15:53.018
My new, favorite
portable Bunsen burner,

15:53.020 --> 15:54.385
Bunny!

15:54.387 --> 15:56.187
All right, everyone, enough fun.

15:56.189 --> 15:57.956
Turn your books to page 20.

15:59.391 --> 16:01.192
-Oh, my God, what is that smell?

16:01.194 --> 16:02.660
Horseradish?

16:02.662 --> 16:04.463
- I don't smell anything.
- You don't!?

16:05.230 --> 16:06.731
How?

16:06.733 --> 16:08.232
[Brooding music]

16:11.137 --> 16:12.604
-Yes, Eggs.

16:12.606 --> 16:14.339
-How come the storm clouds today

16:14.341 --> 16:16.341
don't look like standard
cumulonimbus clouds?

16:16.343 --> 16:18.776
-It's probably because
the thermal rose so quickly.

16:19.344 --> 16:20.811
[Thunder]
- Oh!

16:20.813 --> 16:22.447
Oh!

16:27.219 --> 16:29.053
[Camera shutter clicking]
[School bell ringing]

16:35.026 --> 16:36.494
[Bushes rustling]

16:47.572 --> 16:49.907
-Hey, here are your photos
from last night.

16:49.909 --> 16:51.076
-Thanks, Jonas.

16:51.078 --> 16:52.977
Oh, and sorry for the stealth
exit through the garden.

16:52.979 --> 16:55.045
-Another patrol mystery solved!

16:55.047 --> 16:57.082
-I think we got some good shots
for your portfolio.

16:57.084 --> 16:59.583
And if you need any more copies
anytime just let me know, okay?

16:59.585 --> 17:01.320
- Yeah, for sure.
- Yeah.

17:01.322 --> 17:03.755
-So, are you, uh,
getting back into acting?

17:08.327 --> 17:10.728
I'm telling you:
it was so weird.

17:10.730 --> 17:13.031
I-I could have sworn
I saw something outside

17:13.033 --> 17:14.533
the window in art class.

17:14.535 --> 17:16.801
I had my camera
and I saw something

17:16.803 --> 17:18.336
like, rustling in the trees.

17:18.338 --> 17:19.871
I don't-- I can't even
explain to you. Like--

17:19.873 --> 17:21.473
-BRB.
Emergency.

17:21.475 --> 17:23.007
[Airy music]

17:29.414 --> 17:31.249
-Anyways, like I was saying,

17:31.251 --> 17:33.352
I definitely saw rustling
in the trees, though.

17:33.354 --> 17:36.120
-Or did you fall asleep
watching Twilight Zone again?

17:36.122 --> 17:38.356
-Gotta get a jump
on the pepperoni

17:38.358 --> 17:40.158
before Pudge Patrol
clears it out.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.693
[Students laughing]
[Sigh]

17:42.695 --> 17:44.529
-Come on, let's get outta here.

17:49.568 --> 17:51.902
Well, I guess
we have a new nickname.

17:51.904 --> 17:53.571
-Yeah, this one really stings.

17:53.573 --> 17:55.072
-Screw them.

17:55.074 --> 17:56.774
What do you want to do tonight?

17:56.776 --> 17:58.976
Some light
breaking and entering, perhaps?

17:58.978 --> 18:00.378
[Bathroom door opens]

18:00.380 --> 18:01.847
-MICHELLE:
I hope Tate's okay.

18:01.849 --> 18:04.382
He's obvi my ideal
court king for Formal!

18:04.384 --> 18:06.784
<i>-So, I have some goss
from my brother</i>

18:06.786 --> 18:08.519
<i>who works at the police station.</i>

18:08.521 --> 18:10.722
<i>I could get in
so much trouble for this--</i>

18:10.724 --> 18:12.256
-Dish!

18:12.258 --> 18:14.092
Pinky swear
I won't say anything.

18:14.094 --> 18:16.461
You know you're my BFFesty 4L.

18:16.463 --> 18:18.597
<i>-Well, apparently,</i>

18:18.599 --> 18:21.266
<i>a few officers got called
to Brighton Creek Trail.</i>

18:21.268 --> 18:24.402
<i>They found Tate's school ID,
but no sign of him.</i>

18:24.404 --> 18:26.036
[Ominous music]
- What?

18:26.038 --> 18:28.206
<i>-It's like he evaporated,
or something.</i>

18:28.208 --> 18:29.807
-No.

18:29.809 --> 18:31.109
You're kidding!

18:32.644 --> 18:34.078
-Oh!

18:34.914 --> 18:37.482
Holy shit, Astrid!
Evaporated!

18:37.484 --> 18:39.617
-Lils, it's a common word;

18:39.619 --> 18:41.151
coincidence!

18:41.153 --> 18:42.853
Speaking of, you gotta stop

18:42.855 --> 18:44.623
with the
psychosomatic guilt yelps.

18:44.625 --> 18:47.291
-They're not psychosomatic
and they hurt like hell!

18:48.026 --> 18:49.560
You don't feel different at all?

18:49.562 --> 18:51.962
-No. I mean,
the smell of breakfast

18:51.964 --> 18:54.031
made me extra nauseated
this morning,

18:54.033 --> 18:55.766
but what else is new?

18:55.768 --> 18:58.569
-What about science class?
Horseradish?

18:58.571 --> 19:00.171
- Lils, we didn't do anything.

19:00.173 --> 19:02.707
We burned a Hacky Sack,
danced around the yard

19:02.709 --> 19:04.842
and yelled some stuff
into the universe.

19:05.211 --> 19:06.977
People do it all the time.

19:06.979 --> 19:09.213
-Can we please
check it out tonight?

19:09.215 --> 19:10.981
For science?

19:10.983 --> 19:12.516
[Mysterious music]

19:12.518 --> 19:13.784
[Thunder cracks]

19:13.786 --> 19:17.521
-Now, who here pissed off God
and brought these storm clouds?

19:17.523 --> 19:19.057
-Mom.

19:19.724 --> 19:21.326
-How was school, sweetie?

19:21.328 --> 19:22.993
What's in the envelope?

19:22.995 --> 19:24.595
Those better not be
the headshots

19:24.597 --> 19:26.197
that I told you not to take.

19:26.199 --> 19:27.665
-No, it's just homework.

19:28.267 --> 19:30.268
-I know you wouldn't lie to me.

19:30.270 --> 19:31.936
-Don't really have a choice.

19:31.938 --> 19:33.404
[Thunder rumbles]

19:35.807 --> 19:37.308
[Unsettling music]

19:50.889 --> 19:52.557
<i>-THEATER GAL:
You coming back, Val?</i>

19:52.559 --> 19:55.025
<i>-Yeah, I'll be back
to rehearsals in a moment.</i>

19:55.027 --> 19:56.561
<i>My allergies
are just killing me!</i>

19:56.563 --> 19:58.163
[Crickets chirping]

19:58.165 --> 19:59.697
[Mysterious music]

20:01.634 --> 20:03.401
[Sneezing]
[Coughing]

20:03.403 --> 20:04.902
[Unsettling music]

20:04.904 --> 20:06.503
[Tree leaves rustling]

20:06.505 --> 20:08.005
[Sneezing and coughing
continues]

20:12.377 --> 20:13.912
<i>-TEARJERKER:
Hello,</i>

20:13.914 --> 20:15.579
<i>Valerie.</i>

20:15.780 --> 20:17.382
<i>Alone again,</i>

20:17.384 --> 20:18.984
<i>like always.</i>

20:18.986 --> 20:20.884
<i>It's a shame</i>

20:20.886 --> 20:23.421
<i>that your melodramatic
personality</i>

20:23.423 --> 20:25.523
<i>pushes everyone away.</i>

20:25.525 --> 20:28.726
<i>I could drink you
right up, Valerie.</i>

20:28.728 --> 20:29.928
[Moaning]

20:29.930 --> 20:31.862
<i>In fact, I think I will.</i>

20:31.864 --> 20:33.398
[Crying]

20:33.400 --> 20:35.199
[Unsettling music]

20:35.801 --> 20:37.402
-ASTRID:
Whoa.

20:37.404 --> 20:39.136
What exactly are we looking for?

20:39.405 --> 20:41.138
-LILLY:
Not sure. Um...

20:41.140 --> 20:42.540
[Mysterious music]

20:42.542 --> 20:43.674
[Owl hooting in distance]

20:43.676 --> 20:46.944
Oh, I think that flag marks
where Tate's ID was found.

20:46.946 --> 20:48.079
Ouch!

20:48.081 --> 20:49.813
Oh.

20:49.815 --> 20:51.615
Oh, my leg!

20:51.617 --> 20:53.017
[Gasps]

20:53.019 --> 20:54.485
What is this stuff?

20:54.487 --> 20:56.086
-Uh, like, honestly...

20:56.088 --> 20:57.621
I have no idea.

20:57.623 --> 20:59.157
[Lily groans in pain]

20:59.691 --> 21:01.192
-It's disgusting.

21:02.027 --> 21:03.894
It's so squishy.

21:03.896 --> 21:05.629
-Ach!
Almost smells like...

21:05.631 --> 21:07.131
burnt pickles.

21:07.133 --> 21:08.565
[Astrid sniffs]

21:08.567 --> 21:10.434
-Oh, my God, what is happening?

21:10.436 --> 21:12.569
My leg won't stop
freaking out on me.

21:12.571 --> 21:14.939
It's like it's
being drawn to the goo.

21:21.179 --> 21:22.913
Uh, Astrid?

21:23.314 --> 21:24.783
I think I found something!

21:27.519 --> 21:29.520
-Is that a broken fingernail?

21:32.324 --> 21:34.525
A seven-inch long

21:34.527 --> 21:36.027
broken fingernail?

21:36.661 --> 21:38.195
-Looks like it.

21:38.197 --> 21:39.731
Bag it up.

21:41.333 --> 21:42.933
-Oh, God.
[Leaves rustling]

21:42.935 --> 21:44.468
-Hello?

21:44.670 --> 21:46.237
[Leaves rustling nearby]

21:47.373 --> 21:49.073
-Aah...

21:49.075 --> 21:50.674
[Foreboding music]

21:51.042 --> 21:52.676
[Panicked breathing]

21:52.678 --> 21:54.479
[Both screaming]

21:55.680 --> 21:57.048
-B-b-ack off, buddy!

21:59.217 --> 22:00.885
Oh, shit.

22:00.887 --> 22:02.620
I'm gonna die at the hands
of a hottie with a body.

22:02.622 --> 22:04.889
-BRUTUS: Relax, I'm not
going to kill you.

22:04.891 --> 22:06.024
[Scoffs] I'm actually here
to protect you

22:06.026 --> 22:08.893
from the thing that wants to
kill you, so, you're welcome.

22:08.895 --> 22:10.494
-Wait.
What?

22:10.496 --> 22:12.029
-Who the hell are you
and wh-what do you mean

22:12.031 --> 22:13.531
that thing that wants
to kill us?

22:13.533 --> 22:15.232
-Okay, so, I'm Brutus.

22:15.234 --> 22:18.235
Long story short: a portal
to another dimension was opened.

22:18.237 --> 22:20.905
End-of-the-world type thing:
bad guys, monsters...

22:20.907 --> 22:23.173
The sort of thing
you see in the movies.

22:23.175 --> 22:25.709
The thing is that this portal
wasn't just opened by itself.

22:25.711 --> 22:27.512
No, it was opened by...

22:27.514 --> 22:29.079
you.

22:30.115 --> 22:31.648
B-T-dubs,

22:31.784 --> 22:33.383
who hurt you, hm?

22:33.785 --> 22:35.319
This portal is no joke.

22:35.321 --> 22:38.255
Only humans with severe pain
can open that portal.

22:38.257 --> 22:39.790
-We're stuck in the woods

22:39.792 --> 22:42.426
with a crazy mofo
who thinks monsters are real!

22:44.730 --> 22:46.397
Lilly, run!

22:46.399 --> 22:47.998
-What about that spell you did?

22:48.000 --> 22:49.367
Hm?

22:49.369 --> 22:51.268
- Oh, I told you!
- Okay, what spell?

22:51.270 --> 22:53.137
-Oh, you know,
the one where you were standing

22:53.139 --> 22:55.739
7.263 feet
from each other.

22:55.741 --> 22:57.542
The copper, the fir tree bark

22:57.544 --> 22:58.743
and the pièce de résistance

22:58.745 --> 23:02.046
when you were howling
your intense pain at the moon.

23:02.348 --> 23:04.014
"Ahh..."

23:04.016 --> 23:06.283
-And then we said, "We want you
all to evaporate" backwards!

23:06.285 --> 23:08.285
-What? No.

23:08.287 --> 23:10.287
No, no - only the stuff
that I said.

23:10.289 --> 23:12.090
-Wait, why are we listening
to this lunatic?

23:12.092 --> 23:14.425
-And you really should have
known better than to do it

23:14.427 --> 23:16.927
on the third Sunday of the
ninth month during a pink moon.

23:16.929 --> 23:18.229
Come on...

23:18.231 --> 23:19.763
Since you're the ones
who opened it,

23:19.765 --> 23:21.765
you are also the only ones
who can close it.

23:21.767 --> 23:23.534
Otherwise, humanity sort of...

23:24.636 --> 23:25.969
disappears.

23:25.971 --> 23:27.472
No biggie.

23:27.474 --> 23:30.241
-This cannot be real.
You cannot be real.

23:30.243 --> 23:32.110
We were just messing around!

23:32.112 --> 23:33.777
It was all fake!

23:33.779 --> 23:35.112
We were just blowing off steam

23:35.114 --> 23:37.047
from the hostile jerks
at school!

23:37.049 --> 23:38.515
-Yeah, well, the good news

23:38.517 --> 23:40.050
is that your connection
to the portal

23:40.052 --> 23:42.052
is actually
increasing your senses.

23:42.054 --> 23:43.654
The leg cramps,
the weird smells...

23:43.656 --> 23:45.389
That's your powers kicking in.

23:45.391 --> 23:47.324
-Hey, look, hot guy,

23:47.727 --> 23:49.593
you're dropping an insane amount

23:49.595 --> 23:51.596
of batshit craziness on us.

23:52.330 --> 23:54.264
And why the hell
would we believe you?

23:54.266 --> 23:55.867
-Because I'm from
the dimension you opened.

23:55.869 --> 23:58.202
I'm your guide.
Your-your Brutus.

23:58.204 --> 23:59.803
[Laughs]
Your, um...

23:59.805 --> 24:02.773
your "Giles," in terms
you humans might understand.

24:03.408 --> 24:04.742
-Huh.
Nice try.

24:04.744 --> 24:06.343
-Okay.

24:06.345 --> 24:08.579
Proof. I really hate
this part.

24:08.581 --> 24:10.347
Yeah, messes up the whole 'do.

24:11.249 --> 24:12.816
[Sharp nasal exhale]

24:12.818 --> 24:14.152
[Crackling]

24:18.156 --> 24:20.057
I know:
not a good look.

24:21.426 --> 24:23.094
-Nice special effects makeup.

24:23.728 --> 24:26.297
You tell Tate, or Candace,
or whoever

24:26.565 --> 24:28.433
to kiss my fat ass!

24:28.435 --> 24:31.102
We'll never go to one of
their parties again, hm?

24:31.104 --> 24:33.003
They win!
Come on, Lilly, let's go.

24:33.005 --> 24:35.339
This dude is psycho!
Come on!

24:35.341 --> 24:37.107
-Look, I can't make you stay.

24:37.109 --> 24:39.477
Rule number 6795C,
but you really should know:

24:39.479 --> 24:41.912
the thing that has your friend
is called a Tearjerker

24:41.914 --> 24:43.681
and it targets
literally anything that cries,

24:43.683 --> 24:45.049
for any reason at all.

24:45.051 --> 24:46.383
-We've gotta go.
Let's go!

24:46.385 --> 24:48.785
-And if you happen to be sad AF,

24:48.787 --> 24:51.556
- then it really wants you.
- Come on, Lilly.

24:51.558 --> 24:54.325
It will say to you the deepest,
darkest thing you fear the most.

24:54.327 --> 24:55.993
Oh, and you should really know

24:55.995 --> 24:58.061
your friend only has 26 hours!

24:58.063 --> 25:00.999
-I'm not listening
to a horny guy in the woods!

25:01.934 --> 25:03.501
[Whimpering and crying]

25:03.503 --> 25:05.069
[Foreboding music]

25:13.078 --> 25:14.945
-Why can't I stop crying?

25:14.947 --> 25:16.414
-I don't know.

25:17.082 --> 25:18.815
I can't either.

25:18.817 --> 25:20.317
[Sniffling and sobbing]

25:22.353 --> 25:24.221
-Let all those tears out,

25:24.223 --> 25:26.557
my miserable lovelies!

25:26.559 --> 25:28.225
[Maniacal laughter]

25:28.227 --> 25:29.660
[Thumping techno music]

25:33.599 --> 25:35.332
And I'll tell you why...

25:36.502 --> 25:37.968
you can't stop

25:37.970 --> 25:39.303
crying:

25:40.772 --> 25:42.974
because you're
excellent party guests!

25:44.109 --> 25:45.743
Ahh...

25:45.745 --> 25:48.579
Damn, I love these sweet beats.

25:48.581 --> 25:51.115
-I know this monster thing
is disgusting,

25:51.117 --> 25:53.317
but is he also kind of sexy?

25:53.319 --> 25:55.118
Like a sexy daddy

25:55.120 --> 25:56.987
who deals party drugs?

25:56.989 --> 25:59.023
-Gross, but yes, exactly.

25:59.891 --> 26:01.726
-I know you're
not quite ready yet,

26:01.728 --> 26:04.495
but daddy wants a tear-tini.

26:04.497 --> 26:06.129
[Maniacal laughter]

26:06.131 --> 26:07.831
[Deep sniff and exhale]

26:10.935 --> 26:13.303
I think it might need
a little garnish.

26:14.472 --> 26:15.973
[Woman whimpering]

26:17.141 --> 26:18.543
[Woman crying]

26:21.313 --> 26:22.847
[Scream]

26:22.849 --> 26:24.381
[Squelching]

26:26.819 --> 26:28.686
Perfect.

26:28.688 --> 26:28.752
[Tate screams]

26:28.953 --> 26:36.260
[Organ music]

26:37.161 --> 26:39.096
<i>-CHRISTINE:
Now, speaking of sin...</i>

26:39.098 --> 26:42.500
let's talk about the upcoming
fertile ground for sin:

26:43.301 --> 26:44.769
the Soccer Formal.

26:44.771 --> 26:46.903
And don't give me
that look, okay?

26:46.905 --> 26:48.438
I was young once, too,

26:48.440 --> 26:51.175
and we all know what happens
at those things.

26:51.309 --> 26:53.910
So, I am here to ask you

26:54.245 --> 26:56.347
what would you rather have
inside you:

26:56.848 --> 26:58.449
The Lord's light

26:58.451 --> 27:00.117
or the devil's penis?

27:00.119 --> 27:01.652
-Jesus, Mom.

27:01.654 --> 27:03.120
-Exactly, Jesus.

27:03.122 --> 27:04.589
Ding, ding, ding! Hm.

27:04.591 --> 27:06.123
That's my girl.

27:06.125 --> 27:07.924
You got it, for the win.

27:08.192 --> 27:09.827
Okay, I'll be right back.

27:09.829 --> 27:11.995
Just going to
powder my holy nose.

27:11.997 --> 27:13.430
Hm.

27:15.199 --> 27:16.734
[Conspiratorial music]

27:27.279 --> 27:28.679
[Hushed boom]

27:32.684 --> 27:34.118
[Shaky breathing]

27:35.220 --> 27:36.654
